CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 13, 1958, pg. 7, reads: "Old Time Players Talk About Past - Talent Galore - This is a group of former ball players who, on today's market, would had brought a fancy price in baseball.  The picture was taken at Ted Page's Bowling Alleys in Pittsburgh recently, when Judy Johnson, former great, visited the city.  Left to right: Ted Page, Judy Johnson, Ralph Mellix, Clarence Bruce, Vic Harris, Willis Moody and 'Jap' Washington. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Former Negro League and sandlot baseball players Ted Page, Judy Johnson, Ralph Mellix, Clarence Bruce, Vic Harris, Willis Moody, and Jasper "Jap" Washington, at Page's bowling alley
